**Tests (extend existing 2ku tests + add):**
- Update `TestRetroShowWithMetaStageStillRendersSingleBody`: KEEP all existing body assertions (this is the test that currently asserts the body still renders with a meta stage) and ADD assertions that the output contains `--- retro meta ---` and the sidecar JSON content (e.g. the `scope` key value `cohort` appearing after the meta divider; assert meta divider index > body divider index to lock ordering).
- New `TestRetroShowNoMetaOmitsMetaSection`: capture WITHOUT `--meta-file`, assert `--- retro meta ---` is ABSENT and body still renders (guards the common/no-change path).
- New `TestRetroShowMetaPrettyPrinted`: capture with a single-line `--meta-file` (`{"scope":"cohort","decision":"accepted"}`), assert the show output contains indented JSON (e.g. a line beginning with two spaces + `"scope"`), proving pretty-printing.
- Update `TestRetroListOneRetro`: add `META` to the expected header column set; the existing last-field-is-RFC3339 assertion must still pass (META is before CREATED).
- New `TestRetroListMetaColumn`: capture one retro WITH `--meta-file` and one WITHOUT; assert the list shows `Y` on the meta row and `N` on the no-meta row (match by retro id on each data line). Reuse the existing seeding style (execute "retro" "capture" ... + extractRetroID).
- Failure-mode test (optional but recommended): `TestRetroShowMetaUnreadable` — seed a manifest whose retro-meta stage points at a missing artifact path and assert show fails with an error mentioning `retro meta` (mirrors how body-read failure is implicitly covered). If seeding a corrupt-but-valid manifest is too heavy, omit and rely on parity argument.

**Docs plan:** Update docs/retro.md only (no docs/cli regen): (1) replace the "does not yet render the sidecar" sentence with the new `--- retro meta ---` rendering description (pretty-printed JSON, after the body); (2) add `META` row to the list-columns table and update the example list/show output blocks. docs/log.md needs no change (justified above). Run `make docs`/`docs-check`/`docs-reality` in the Docs phase to confirm no generated drift.

**Risks:**
- list-column addition is the one decision a reviewer seat may contest (column-stability vs added signal); it is cleanly separable and documented, with a fall-back to show-only.
- `json.Indent` on already-stored bytes: guarded with a raw-bytes fall-back, so no failure path is introduced.
- Trailing-newline handling between body and meta dividers: the body is printed verbatim (may or may not end in newline); the meta divider is printed with Fprintln so it always starts on its own line — confirm body content typically ends with a newline (test fixtures do). Low risk; if a fixture body lacks a trailing newline the divider still prints on a fresh line because the existing body block uses Fprint and the meta block opens with Fprintln of the divider — acceptable.

