## PLAN-GATE CORRECTION (Tier-1 gate, 3-seat: codex BLOCK verified-true, gemini+Opus GO)
codex caught a real show-format edge, verified at internal/cli/retro.go:381: the body is rendered with `fmt.Fprint(out, string(bodyBytes))` which adds NO trailing newline (only the pointer-storage branch at :383 ends in "\n"). If a retro body lacks a trailing newline, the new `--- retro meta ---` divider (fmt.Fprintln) would glue onto the body's last line:
    last body line--- retro meta ---
which violates the section-on-its-own-line format. (Recurring Defect Class #4: output must land at the exact rendered slot.)

REQUIRED FIX in the show-rendering path: before emitting the `--- retro meta ---` divider, guarantee the body output ended with a newline. Concretely: in the content-storage branch, if `len(bodyBytes) > 0 && bodyBytes[len(bodyBytes)-1] != '\n'`, emit a `fmt.Fprintln(out)` (single newline) before the meta divider. The pointer-storage branch already ends in "\n" so no extra newline there. Equivalent: track a `bodyEndedWithNewline` bool and conditionally Fprintln. Do NOT unconditionally add a blank line (would change today's no-meta output for bodies that DO end in "\n" — keep no-meta output byte-identical).

REQUIRED TEST: add `TestRetroShowMetaBodyNoTrailingNewline` — capture a retro with --meta-file whose body file has NO trailing newline, assert the rendered output contains "\n--- retro meta ---\n" (divider on its own line, not glued to the body). Keep the existing no-trailing-newline-WITHOUT-meta behavior unchanged.

Minor (non-blocking) impl note from codex: if using bytes.HasSuffix you must add the `bytes` import; the simple index check above needs no new import. `encoding/json` is already imported.

All other plan decisions stand unchanged (role-based detection, read-pattern parity "retro meta: %w", json.Indent + raw fallback, META-before-CREATED list column keeping CREATED last + RFC3339 assertion intact, no new flag → no docs/cli regen, docs/retro.md-only prose change, docs/log.md no-op).
